      <description>&lt;p&gt;I have created &#xA;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://yasuit21.github.io/en/hypo/&#34;&gt;a page where users can interactively explore the three-dimensional distribution of earthquake hypocenters and fault geometries&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&#xA;.&#xA;At present, the page covers the two earthquakes in our publications: &#xA;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://doi.org/10.1029/2024JB030233&#34; title=&#34;Sawaki et al. (2025, JGR)&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener noreferrer&#34;&gt;2024 Mw 7.5 Noto Peninsula, central Japan&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&#xA;, and &#xA;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://doi.org/10.1186/s40623-025-02311-9&#34; title=&#34;Sawaki et al. (2025, EPS)&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener noreferrer&#34;&gt;August 2024 Mw 5.0 western Kanagawa, eastern Japan&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&#xA;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
